description.plain:
Shylo Batchelor Ashby Milwood (b. 20 March 1996), popularly known as Russ Millions (short for ‘Russian’, name changed due to controversy with the American rapper Russ) is a rapper from Lewisham, South London. He is a member of the Splash Music Group (SMG) drill collective.

Russ caused controversy when he dissed 814 rapper Showkey in his tune with Maj and SP, “Tribute 811”. The track came a week just after Showkey and Mdot were stabbed to death. The track was a a reply to Showkey’s dissing of YB, a member of SMG, in “Vavavoom”.

He is also known for the popularisation of the dance ‘'Gun Lean’'.

In January 2019, Pressplay (popular UK Drill outlet) renamed Russ' name on all of his videos to ‘Rush’. Russ himself was not happy with Pressplay for doing it. Pressplay claimed they were forced to change Russ' name after being asked by American rapper Russ' legal team. Most of Russ' videos are blocked in the US and Canada, possibly related to the name problem. This was later changed back, and Russ now goes by ‘Russ Millions’.

description.plain:
“Big Shark” is South London Drill artist Russ Millions‘ highly anticipated follow up from his March 2021 viral Number 1 single “Body” with Tion Wayne.

Following the November 2020 incident where Hackney, East London rapper Dutchavelli’s social media was hacked, an Instagram DM was leaked between him and his sister Stefflon Don, in which she compared Russ to “Baby Shark”, the viral German kids song.

Capitalising off being dragged into the limelight, in February 2021, Russ previewed a song called “Baby Shark” on his Instagram. In April 2021 during an Interview on THE ZEZE MILLZ SHOW, Russ confirmed that “Baby Shark” would be his next single release – the name later changed to “Big Shark”, possibly to avoid copyright strikes.

On the 20th of June 2021, Russ posted an official teaser for the song on social media, which unveiled Stefflon Don to feature on the video:
